Bug 2047704 - Fix IMAP messages wrongly deleted on cross-server move failure when offline store is disabled. r=mkmelin

When moving messages or folders from an IMAP account to Local Folders with
offline storage disabled, the copy takes the batch path via
CopyMessagesTo(), which calls nsImapService::CopyMessages with
nsImapOnlineToOfflineMove. This action fetches all messages then issues
STORE +FLAGS (\Deleted \Seen) for all of them — before any data has been
written to the destination mbox. If the local write subsequently fails
(e.g. "out of space"), the source messages are already gone from the
server.

When offline storage is enabled, the one-at-a-time path via
CopyMessageTo() is used instead, which reads from local offline store and
never invokes the IMAP protocol handler, so the bug does not manifest.

Fix this by decoupling the two uses of the isMove parameter in
nsMsgLocalMailFolder: the CopyMessageStreamListener still gets isMove=true
so EndMove fires and handles source deletion with proper error gating, but
the source message service is passed moveMessage=false so it uses
nsImapOnlineToOfflineCopy instead — avoiding the independent deletion.

Since nsImapOnlineToOfflineMove is no longer reachable, remove the
associated dead code from nsImapService, nsImapProtocol, and
nsImapMailFolder.

Also extend test_moveCopyFoldersAcrossServers.js to verify that after a
successful cross-server folder move, source messages are actually deleted
(source folder should be empty). Previously the test only checked the
destination side.

Differential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D311732


